                <componentInstanceProperties>
                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-size: 13pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(67, 67, 67); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Scheduled Data Export&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(116, 116, 116); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;The post-deployment script that runs during the installation of this package should have scheduled the Apex class called &quot;PayPalDataScheduler&quot; to automatically execute daily at 3 AM. Please confirm that the scheduled job, named &quot;PayPalDataScheduler - Everyday 3AM,&quot; exists in the Setup &amp;gt; Scheduled Jobs section. Feel free to adjust the configuration of this scheduled job to suit your specific requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(116, 116, 116); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Please ensure that the &quot;PayPal_Data_Permissions&quot; Permission Set is assigned to the user responsible for scheduling this job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67); font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 13pt;&quot;&gt;One-Time Data Export for Existing PayPal Transactions (Optional)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(116, 116, 116); font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;If you wish to export existing transactions from your PayPal account to Salesforce, please follow the steps below before running the provided anonymous script:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Adjust the &apos;startDate&apos; and &apos;endDate&apos; to suit your specific requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Note that this script will execute a series of queueable Apex jobs to export your data. The number of jobs in the chain is determined by the specified &apos;startDate&apos; and &apos;endDate&apos;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;You can abort the execution of the job chain at any time by setting the custom metadata &apos;salesforce_paypal_transaction_settings.Killcurrentdatamigrationfailsafe&apos; value to &apos;true&apos;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(116, 116, 116); font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Execute the anonymous script as follows:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;// Set the start and end dates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;Datetime startDate = Date.newInstance(2023, 10, 01).addDays(1);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;Datetime endDate = Date.newInstance(2023, 10, 31).addDays(1);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;// Queue the jobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;System.enqueueJob(new PayPalDataExportQueueable(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;true, startDate, endDate, 1, 200,&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;Boolean.valueOf(Salesforce_PayPal_Transaction_Settings__mdt.getInstance(&apos;ExcludeAccountContact&apos;).Value__c)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Roboto Mono&amp;quot;, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt;&quot;&gt;));&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(116, 116, 116); font-family: &amp;quot;Salesforce Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;To monitor the progress of the job chain, navigate to Setup &amp;gt; Apex Jobs. Ensure that all the jobs are marked as complete. Afterward, visit the PayPal Transactions Tab to verify if all PayPal transactions have been successfully exported. If not, review the logs and adjust the &apos;startDate&apos; and &apos;endDate&apos; values in the script as needed, then rerun the script.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
                </componentInstanceProperties>
                <componentName>flexipage:richText</componentName>
                <identifier>flexipage_richText3</identifier>
            </componentInstance>
